===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|又|t1=hand|中|t2=a flagpole with a drum|ls=ic}} – flag in hand > to perform one's job. Compare {{zh-l|*吏}}. Furthermore, both characters are related to {{zh-l|*史}}, which is a variant without the horizontal stroke on top.

===Etymology===
Exopassive of {{och-l|士|to give or carry out an assignment; to serve}}, literally “what has been assigned” ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Alternatively, based on {{zh-ref|Gong (2000)}}, STEDT derives it from {{der|zh|sit-pro|*r-dzas||thing}}, whence {{cog|my|စာ||thing}} and {{cog|bo|རྫས||thing, object, matter}}. <!-- not Gong (2001), as STEDT wrongly cites -->

